one.π\">π</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Biproducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.Bicone.ι\">ι</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span>)</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Category/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.CategoryStruct.id\">CategoryStruct.id</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Biproducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.Bicone.pt\">pt</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Limits/Shapes/Biproducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.Bicone.IsBilimit\">IsBilimit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"In a preadditive category, we can construct a biproduct for `f : J → C` from\nany bicone `b` for `f` satisfying `total : ∑ j : J, b.π j ≫ b.ι j = 𝟙 b.X`.\n\n(That is, such a bicone is a limit cone and a colimit cocone.)\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Preadditive/Biproducts.html#CategoryTheory.Limits.isBilimitOfTotal","kind":"def","line":85,"name":"CategoryTheory.Limits.isBilimitOfTotal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Preadditive/Biproducts.lean#L85-L121"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.BigOperators.Group.Finset.Piecewise","Mathlib.Algebra.Group.Ext","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Preserves.Shapes.BinaryProducts","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Preserves.Shapes.Biproducts","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Preserves.Shapes.Products","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Preadditive.Basic","Mathlib.Tactic.Abel"],"instances":[{"className":"Subsingleton","name":"CategoryTheory.subsingleton_preadditive_of_hasBinaryBiproducts","typeNames":["CategoryTheory.Preadditive"]}],"name":"Mathlib.Categ